```java
private StringBuffer appendQuotedString(String pattern, ParsePosition pos,
        StringBuffer appendTo, boolean escapingOn) {
    int start = pos.getIndex();
    char[] c = pattern.toCharArray();
    int lastHold = start;

    while (pos.getIndex() < pattern.length()) {
        char currentChar = c[pos.getIndex()];

        // Handle escaped quotes
        if (escapingOn && currentChar == ESCAPED_QUOTE.charAt(0) && 
            pos.getIndex() + 1 < pattern.length() && 
            c[pos.getIndex() + 1] == QUOTE) {
            appendTo.append(c, lastHold, pos.getIndex() - lastHold);
            appendTo.append(QUOTE);
            pos.setIndex(pos.getIndex() + 2); // Move past the escaped quote
            lastHold = pos.getIndex(); // Update lastHold to the new position
            continue;
        }

        // Handle normal quotes
        if (currentChar == QUOTE) {
            appendTo.append(c, lastHold, pos.getIndex() - lastHold); // Append the text before the quote
            next(pos); // Move to the next character (the quote)
            return appendTo; // End processing upon encountering a closing quote
        }

        // Move to the next character
        next(pos);
    }

    // If we reach the end of the pattern without closing the quote
    throw new IllegalArgumentException(
            "Unterminated quoted string at position " + start);
}
```

### Key Changes Made
1. **Correctly handle escaped quotes**: The logic for detecting an escaped quote now checks both the current character and the next character.
2. **Consistently manage `lastHold`**: This variable tracks the last position where text should be appended, and it is updated appropriately after appending the text before a quote or an escaped quote.
3. **Properly handle loop exit conditions**: The loop checks if the current index is within the bounds of the string and processes characters accordingly.

This revision should ensure that the function correctly handles quoted strings while considering escape sequences.

